IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDescription: The Community School of Naples is committed to academic excellence. We provide our students with a broad range of personal opportunities within a caring and respectful environment.The School prepares students to become independent thinkers and lifelong learners who strive to realize their full potential. In support of our vision, we apply innovative thinking and technology within a rigorous curriculum; focus on involved citizenship in the world at large; and rely on the commitment of our parents, the dedication of great teachers and the involvement of our students.

IRS990.Description: CSN is committed to academic excellence. The school is recognized for its comprehensive college preparatory program that blends rigor with a commitment to individual growth and development. From PK to 12th grade, 722 students take part in a curriculum that reflects the highest standards of independent schools, on a 110-acre, $40 million campus including a media center, field house and playing fields. Advanced placement courses are available in every curricular area. Of our dedicated, experienced faculty, more than half have advanced degrees. class sizes are small, allowing for close relationships with faculty and ongoing assessment. Students may participate in numerous activities involving music, the arts, sports, mathcounts and mu alpha theta, model congress, model un and foreign language competitions. The school prepares students to become independent thinkers and lifelong learners who strive to realize their full potential.

Form990ScheduleIPartIV.Identifier: Procedure for Monitoring Grants in the U.S.:
Form990ScheduleIPartIV.Explanation: Schedule I, Part I, Line 2: Financial aid is granted based on need and enrollment, and must be applied on a year to year basis by submitting detailed financial information and a copy of the prior year tax return . Senior Systems software is used for student billing, and financial aid award application. Accountant processes monthly statements and payments. All payments are recorded daily by the receptionist upon receipt, and forwarded to Accountant for crediting to individual student accounts. Accounts Receivable is reviewed weekly by the CFO,and general ledger budget for tuition revenue and financial aid, by division, is monitored by the Finance Mgr on a monthly basis.

Form990ScheduleJPartIII.Explanation: The Head of School is the only officer that receives these types of benefits. During 2010 he had a $20,000 discretionary allowance of which included $4,080 of athletic dues. Reimbursement for any allowance expenses were approved by the division supervisor and not included in his taxable income. He also received $6,125 of gross-up pay, a $25,000 housing allowance, and $13,200 in car allowance which were included in his taxable income.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 11
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE CFO REVIEWS WITH THE FINANCE COMMITTEE CHAIR BEFORE FINAL APPROVAL. UPON FINAL APPROVAL THE CFO SIGNS THE TAX RETURN.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 12c
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The background of each nominated trustee is thoroughly reviewed for conflict of interests prior to submission of that individual as a board candidate. There is no written monitoring of possible conflict, but annually the Board Chair reminds each member of their fiduciary responsibilities.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 15
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE CFO AND CEO'S Compensation IS COMPARED TO other SIMILAR schools and is taken into consideration, public and private schools, from surveys available online, along with cost of living and the approved budgets, which are based on enrollment. Both of these positions compensation are compared to the compensation statistics from the NAIS and from FCIS (national and Florida private school organizations) and their relativities are considered before any adjustments are made.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section C, line 19
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The financials are forwarded to Dunn & Brad annually. CSN provides an annual report to families and faculty regarding the overall state of the school, and periodically schedules State of the School conferences WHICH ARE open to the public. Upon request, the audited financials are made available.
The process of assuming responsibility for oversight of the audit of the organization's financial statements and selection of an independent accountant has not changed from the prior year.
